# Business Requirements Gathering for BI Reports

### **1. Identify Key Stakeholders**

This report is intened for technical recruiter/employers to review. The report will be formatted as a consumer report to easily navigating project findings and summary.

### **2. Define Reporting Objectives**

 It is noted that the dataset is hosted on the kaggle.com platform and I was not able to naviagte key objective for the dataset. 

## Understanding Why the Report Is Needed. Clarify the business purpose behind analyzing this dataset. Objectives for this dataset include:

    - Improving order fulfillment efficiency

    - Understanding customer purchasing behavior

    - Monitoring sales performance across products, categories, or regions

    - Identifying logistics bottlenecks (shipping delays, delivery failures)

    - Evaluating supplier performance and inventory flow

    - Reducing operational costs in the supply chain

## Identify Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
Based on the dataset’s structure (orders, products, customers, logistics), relevant KPIs include:

Possible KPIs
  -  Total revenue (from price + shipping_charges)

  - Average order value

  - On‑time delivery rate (order_delivered_timestamp vs. order_estimated_delivery_date)

  - Customer lifetime value (CLV)

  - Payment success rate

  - Category‑level sales
   
